flowRoot.flowPara: Your muscles are not stressed enough to grow bigger in 6 minutes.
The high tempo and inadequate time to learn the proper execution of a movement can significantly increase the risk of injury.
Once the body adapts to a certain activity it doesn't require that much energy to perform. 6mins do not leave enough room to break from the plateaus.
Roughly it translates to false sense of effort that accompanies when you see sweat on your shirt after jumping for 6 minutes straight. It didn't build muscle, it didn't made you lose fat.
High intensity workouts can cause hyperglycemia or raised blood sugar in obese or people who are insulin resistant or are fairly new to working out.
